sorry, vocalizations

00:13:16.890 --> 00:13:19.010
and we keep records of these vocalizations

00:13:19.010 --> 00:13:20.750
where a subordinate individual will

00:13:20.750 --> 00:13:22.830
pant grunt to a dominant individual.

00:13:22.830 --> 00:13:25.750
And Tumbo actually overtook
that alpha position

00:13:25.750 --> 00:13:29.330
from Farafa there about two years ago.

00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:33.300
And so, females actually do
hunt some in this community

00:13:33.300 --> 00:13:35.030
or at least enough to be considered

00:13:35.030 --> 00:13:37.480
among the top 10 Fongoli hunters.

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:40.340
And also I'd like to point out that

00:13:40.340 --> 00:13:42.810
we have a tie right now
for the very top hunter

00:13:42.810 --> 00:13:44.903
and one is the alpha male, that's David.

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:49.900
He is tied for the top
hunting position with Siberut

00:13:49.900 --> 00:13:52.507
and some of you will be
happy to know that Siberut

00:13:52.507 --> 00:13:54.750
who is pictured there is not only

00:13:54.750 --> 00:13:57.440
the oldest hunter in the
group, he's oldest male

00:13:57.440 --> 00:13:59.863
but he's also the lowest
ranking male as well.

00:14:01.010 --> 00:14:04.100
And then if you look at female
hunting behavior in general

00:14:04.100 --> 00:14:06.360
females, almost all females hunt

00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:08.210
and almost all males hunt as well

00:14:08.210 --> 00:14:10.010
so they hunt about what you would expect

00:14:10.010 --> 00:14:12.520
or at least their participation
in hunting overall

00:14:12.520 --> 00:14:15.200
is what you would expect based
on their their membership

00:14:15.200 --> 00:14:17.463
in the Fongoli community.

00:14:20.170 --> 00:14:23.340
I wanted to look, talk a little
bit about Fongoli hunting

00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:29.540
and the context of female
hunting across study sites.

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:31.010
So, Ian talked about that some

00:14:31.010 --> 00:14:34.840
and I've used data from
his work and others

00:14:34.840 --> 00:14:36.810
to look at Fongoli female hunting

00:14:36.810 --> 00:14:39.470
and in fact, there are females elsewhere

00:14:39.470 --> 00:14:41.520
that also engage in
quite a bit of hunting.

00:14:41.520 --> 00:14:44.150
In fact, females at
Mahale hunt a little more

00:14:44.150 --> 00:14:46.120
than females at Fongoli if you look at

00:14:46.120 --> 00:14:49.210
Fongoli female hunting behavior overall.

00:14:49.210 --> 00:14:51.100
And then when you look at tool use

00:14:51.100 --> 00:14:54.630
you see that Fongoli
females do hunt quite a bit

00:14:54.630 --> 00:14:56.920
almost half of the tool-assisted hunting

00:14:56.920 --> 00:14:58.320
at Fongoli is by females.

00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:02.350
And again remember that we
have fewer females at Fongoli,

00:15:02.350 --> 00:15:05.540
we don't follow females
systematically like we do males.

00:15:05.540 --> 00:15:08.770
And so one question as to why females hunt

00:15:08.770 --> 00:15:11.343
is basically as David started out with,

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:14.150
you know, it's probably no surprise that

00:15:14.150 --> 00:15:17.600
the chimps gained a lot
of nutrition from hunting,

00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:20.310
but I think perhaps a more
interesting question is

00:15:20.310 --> 00:15:22.920
why females don't hunt
more at other sites.

00:15:22.920 --> 00:15:25.840
And Ian talked about some
of these issues as well

00:15:25.840 --> 00:15:28.350
that I'll pursue right now.

00:15:28.350 --> 00:15:30.993
And so, if you looked
at for example theft,

00:15:32.710 --> 00:15:34.820
there's not a lot of theft at Fongoli

00:15:34.820 --> 00:15:38.170
so when I use the word share
I'm referring to basically

00:15:38.170 --> 00:15:40.600
the last three categories I
think that David talked about.

00:15:40.600 --> 00:15:45.330
So active food transfer
but not theft, right,

00:15:45.330 --> 00:15:47.290
and passive food transfer, et cetera.

00:15:47.290 --> 00:15:50.000
So I consider theft to
be a different category

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:52.210
and at Fongoli you have very little theft.

00:15:52.210 --> 00:15:55.230
The only thought we've seen involves

00:15:55.230 --> 00:15:58.270
two different alpha males,
so very little theft.

00:15:58.270 --> 00:16:00.840
Whereas at other sites you
do have quite a bit of theft

00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:03.763
and so I believe as Ian said,

00:16:05.450 --> 00:16:08.600
females don't have incentive
to hunt at some sites.

00:16:08.600 --> 00:16:10.900
At Fongoli there definitely is incentive

00:16:10.900 --> 00:16:15.600
and not only females but this
is a little video of again

00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:17.510
that lower-ranking male.

00:16:17.510 --> 00:16:19.650
So out of 13 males he's number 13.

00:16:19.650 --> 00:16:21.710
He's the oldest male, that's Siberut.

00:16:21.710 --> 00:16:24.830
So he's walking by a number of adult males

00:16:24.830 --> 00:16:27.220
with this bushbuck fawn that he's captured

00:16:27.220 --> 00:16:31.050
and no one makes any
attempt to take it from him.

00:16:31.050 --> 00:16:33.430
He had actually been eating
on that fawn for over an hour

00:16:33.430 --> 00:16:35.590
and he had a number of
individuals sitting around

00:16:35.590 --> 00:16:38.210
basically begging, he
didn't share with them.

00:16:38.210 --> 00:16:40.660
And as he moves off
you'll see that there's

00:16:40.660 --> 00:16:42.500
another older male that will follow him

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:44.303
and this is his ally Bandit.

00:16:49.486 --> 00:16:50.940
Where's Bandit?

00:16:50.940 --> 00:16:52.640
There he is.

00:16:52.640 --> 00:16:54.540
Calmly following his buddy Siberut out.

00:16:54.540 --> 00:16:57.690
And so, he did end up sharing with Bandit.

00:16:57.690 --> 00:17:02.690
So not only do you see
some sort of concept

00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:05.100
well, I hate to say concept of ownership

00:17:05.100 --> 00:17:05.970
but you see tolerance.

00:17:05.970 --> 00:17:09.010
So tolerance of possession of prey

00:17:10.570 --> 00:17:12.870
by dominant males of these
low ranking individuals,

00:17:12.870 --> 00:17:14.910
females and also lower ranking males.

00:17:14.910 --> 00:17:16.880
So I think that at
Fongoli you actually have

00:17:16.880 --> 00:17:17.900
the incentive to hunt.

00:17:17.900 --> 00:17:20.730
It's one of the reasons that
you see so much hunting,

00:17:20.730 --> 00:17:23.113
at least tool-assisted hunting in females.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:25.860
I wanna show it a slightly different way.

00:17:25.860 --> 00:17:28.400
So, these are the same top 10 hunters

00:17:28.400 --> 00:17:30.720
but rather than being expressed

00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:33.100
in the number of prey that they brought in

00:17:33.100 --> 00:17:34.990
this is the number of kilograms

00:17:34.990 --> 00:17:37.520
or estimated kilograms of meat, right?

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:39.640
And so, you see that David has jumped up

00:17:39.640 --> 00:17:41.390
to number one position there.

00:17:41.390 --> 00:17:42.860
It depends on what you hunt

00:17:42.860 --> 00:17:45.710
and almost everybody hunts
bush babies except K.L.,

00:17:45.710 --> 00:17:47.680
we've never seen him capture a bush baby.

00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:49.540
But what's interesting is you see that

00:17:49.540 --> 00:17:52.250
the third top hunter there

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:54.180
at least in terms of prey captures,

00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:56.040
Lupin has fallen quite low

00:17:56.040 --> 00:17:58.740
because he does seem to
specialize on bush babies.

00:17:58.740 --> 00:18:00.800
So the females really didn't
change positions at all,

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:02.460
they're still in the top 10

00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:04.290
but you do see a lot of variation.

00:18:04.290 --> 00:18:06.320
So that's something that
we're looking at now

00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:09.970
and so, I wanted to talk
just a little bit about

00:18:09.970 --> 00:18:14.693
what females can provide in
terms of transfer or sharing.

00:18:16.450 --> 00:18:21.450
And we, so far this is still
preliminary to some degree.

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:24.770
We've looked at sharing or
food transfer by females

00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:27.490
and again I'm considering
David's categories

00:18:27.490 --> 00:18:29.630
of active transfer, passive transfer

00:18:29.630 --> 00:18:32.190
and scrounging but tolerated scrounging,

00:18:32.190 --> 00:18:35.540
and I'm not considering a theft
in this category in females

00:18:35.540 --> 00:18:38.620
actually shared with other individuals

00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:40.510
more often they did with their offspring.

00:18:40.510 --> 00:18:43.970
So that's something that
we're exploring right now.

00:18:43.970 --> 00:18:47.860
And basically I would argue that females

00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:52.820
